recent_articles.title: AMD bull and bear react to Q2 earnings
recent_articles.summary:
Advanced Micro Devices (AMD) stock is under pressure after the chipmaker reported mixed second quarter results, with sales beating expectations as earnings were slightly light.

Benchmark Company managing director and senior semiconductor research analyst Cody Acree explains why he views AMD as the "only game in town" to compete with Nvidia (NVDA), while Tematica Research chief investment officer Chris Versace outlines why he's hesitant on the stock, highlighting names like Broadcom (AVGO) and Marvell (MRVL) instead.
